main event: Two round, red and green objects were observed in Syracuse, New York in 1955. The objects appeared to change colors and were larger than navigational lights.
interesting points: Two objects were reported, and they were moving from west to east.
The flashing red and green lights suggested the possibility of aircraft, and it was plotted by the local GOC.
The report includes photographs of the objects.
The conclusion was that the objects were probably balloons or aircraft, with insufficient data for a definite evaluation.
sighted object: two round, red and green objects
